dxf2svg.util
Class TableLineType

java.lang.Object
  dxf2svg.util.TableLineType
public final class TableLineType
extends java.lang.Object

This object, in many ways, is subserviant to the TableLayer object. It basically handles the line patterns found on a particular layer in DXF.

Version:
1.02 - September 5, 2002
Author:
Andrew Nisbet

toAttributeString

public java.lang.String toAttributeString(double scale)
This next method is used when you have the unique case of an object whose lineType differs from it's layer's lineType. I noticed this with an arc that took all layer information except line type so when toString() was called it output the wrong string and the svg was drawn incorrectly (or not at all.) This will add it when it is the only attribute on an element.
